css selectors ✅ ( element selector, class selector, id selector, universal selector)
    element selector ✅( representaed as p(for para and so on)) ( it is used to select the element by its name and apply css properties to it )
    class selector ✅(representated as . ) ( it is used to select the element by its class name and apply css properties to it ) 
    id selector ✅( representated as # ) ( it is used to select the element by its id name and apply css properties to it )
    universal selector ✅( representated as * ) ( it is used to select all the elements in the html file and apply css properties to it )
understanding width and height in css in id selector ✅ ( we can set width and height of an element using css properties width and height )
    ( we can set width and height in different units like px, %, em, rem, vw, vh etc )
    ( px: it is a fixed unit, it is not responsive )
    ( %: (isme screen ke according hota h aur isme batana easy hota h ki kitna chahiye h )it is a relative unit, it is responsive )
    ( em: it is a relative unit, it is based on the font size of the element )
    ( rem: it is a relative unit, it is based on the font size of the root element )
    ( vw: it is a relative unit, it is based on the width of the viewport )
    ( vh: it is a relative unit, it is based on the height of the viewport )   
understanding margin and padding in css in id selector ✅ ( we can set margin and padding of an element using css properties margin and padding )
    ( margin: it is the space of elemet ke bhar ka, it creates space between the element and other elements )
    ( padding: it is the space inside the element, it creates space between the content of the element and the border of the element )
    ( we can set margin and padding in different units like px, %, em, rem, vw, vh etc )
    ( we can set margin and padding in different directions like top, right, bottom, left )
    ( we can set margin and padding in shorthand property like margin: 10px 20px 30px 40px; (top right bottom left) )
    ( we can set margin and padding in shorthand property like margin: 10px 20px; (top and bottom , right and left) )
    ( we can set margin and padding in shorthand property like margin: 10px; (all sides) )